This paper deals with fair division, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic decision theory (cs.AI). The problem involves dividing objects among agents, which can be modeled as a data structure (cs.DS). The authors propose online division rules, which can be seen as machine learning algorithms (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of these rules in terms of expected utility, which is a central concept in economics and mechanism design (cs.EC).
